<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Although we have not studied the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Snellen van Vollenhoven" authorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Lophyrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lophyrus catocalus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catocalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Lophyrus catocalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the interpretation of its taxonomic status is possible after referring to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gussakovskij’s">Gussakovskij's</normalizedToken>
description of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="G." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. verticalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="verticalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">G. verticalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other publications cited above. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Pschorn-Walcher, H" editor="Schwenke, W" journalOrPublisher="Paul Parey, Hamburg und Berlin, 4: 4 - 196" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="232 - 234" refId="B154" refString="Pschorn-Walcher, H, 1982. Unterordnung Symphyta, Pflanzenwespen. In: Schwenke, W, Ed., Die Forstschaedlinge Europas. Paul Parey, Hamburg und Berlin, 4: 4-196: 232 - 234" title="Unterordnung Symphyta, Pflanzenwespen." volumeTitle="Die Forstschaedlinge Europas." year="1982">Pschorn-Walcher (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Viitasaari, M" journalOrPublisher="Department of Agricultural and Forest Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 79" refId="B188" refString="Viitasaari, M, Varama, M, 1987. Sahapistiaeiset 4. Havupistiaeiset (Diprionidae). Reports, University of Helsinki. Department of Agricultural and Forest Zoology 10: 1 - 79" title="Sahapistiaeiset 4. Havupistiaeiset (Diprionidae). Reports, University of Helsinki." volume="10" year="1987">Viitasaari and Varama (1987)</bibRefCitation>
that the two forms are an expression of individual variability, linked to population differences with a geographical component. Accordingly, we treat 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Snellen van Vollenhoven" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Gilpinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gilpinia catocala" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catocala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Gilpinia catocala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="G." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. pallida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">G. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
